@node introduction "XTRU v2.1 - Introduction"
Welcome to XTreme Racing Util,

The reason for this little utility is because some versions of XTR cant load
track files crunched with the CrM2 format. Like us, a lot of people decrunch
all the track,objects...etc files to be able to play these, and some people
probably did not even know about this problem at all.

This is where XTRU comes in, it will convert all Track,Object,Tile..etc
files from CrM2 to XPKZ and back again if need be. Also you can decrunch the
files i.e. if you decrunch Misc/CarTypes you can edit the default values for
all the cars. XTR will still load any of its game files if they happen to be
decrunched, but please note that this utility cant crunch any file that you
decrunch at this time. Although it probably will in the updated version.

XTRU has only been tested on `XTR v1.0', `XTR v1.1b Aminet Upgrade' and
the `XTR Data Disk v1.1 Upgrade (Type A)'.

The newest version does not have the same trouble with the `CrM2' format
as the earlier versions. The only other problem we can think of is track
versions. At this time XTRU has only been tested on track versions:-

                  2.11, 2.12, 2.13, 3.00 & 3.01

If you have other versions please do send them to us, so we can update
XTRU, of course only if the copyright allows.
@endnode

@node req "XTRU - Requirements"
XTRU - Requirements
===================

All you need is a hard drive, a copy of XTR and the CrM.lirary if you want
to use the packing features of XTRU. The un/packing functions require quite
large amounts of memory, especially unpacking without the CrM.library
installed.


@endnode

@node Installation "XTRU - Installation"
How to install XTRU
===================

XTRU has been developed for HD users and must be used from Workbench.

Sorry floppy owners :-(

We have written a install script, so for a easy life just click the icon.

Or if you wish you can just copy the XTRU draw to where you want it, Maybe
in your XTR draw might be a good place. Then you must Assign `XTRU:' to the
place you copied XTRU  to your `user-startup' for example:-

    Assign XTRU: Work:games/XTR/XTRU

This is all the install script does anyway so we recommend you use that.

@endnode

@node usage "XTRU - Usage"
It's Installed, What now?
=========================

The first time you run XTRU you will be asked to take it into your main XTR
draw so it can find the needed files. Please note this is the main XTR draw
where you see the files `FrontEnd' and `Race', although this is checked by
XTRU just to make sure you get it right. Next XTRU will evaluate all tracks
you have installed, if any are unplayable they are moved into the `Storage'
directory.

Once XTRU has been run, a window will open with a list view and some gadgets

The list view is used to show info about the loaded track file:-

            Track name           : Name of loaded track

            Pack Type            : Is it crunched? If so what type

            Version              : Track version number(?)

            Objects              : These two list objects
            Extras               : used by the track

            Tiles                : Tiles used by the track

            BackGround           : Track background file

            LayOut               : Track layout file

            World                : Track world file

            Sound FX             : Track sounds

Any OBJECTS,TILES or BACKGROUND marked with a `*' means these files are not
installed, therefore you can't play this track.

If LAYOUT or WORLD are marked with `**' this means these files are missing
but XTR will still let you play these tracks, as these images are only used
whilst selecting what track to play on and not during the race itself. If
WORLD is marked as `N/A' the track does not need this file anyway.
DEATHMATCH tracks do not use WORLD files.

Sound FX, as far as v2.11, v2.12, v2.13, v3.00 track files are concerned this
is always `N/A' but v3.01 tracks show `Default.Sfx'. I dont no why this is
at this moment in time because the newest version of XTR that uses sound
files does not take this seting into account, it uses the preset sound file
as selected in the setup menu. This is being looked into though.

  The gadgets :-
               @{" Load " link gtload}           : Load a track and view info.

               @{" Unpack " link gtunpack}         : Unpack any XPKZ or CrM2 file.

               @{" Pack " link gtpack}           : Pack any file to XPKZ or CrM2 format.

               @{" About " link gtabout}          : About XTRU

               @{" Quit " link gtquit}           : Exit XTRU

               @{" XPKZ > CrM2 " link gtxtc}    : Convert Track and all Object,Tile,Background
                                 : ,LayOut and World files to CrM2 format.

               @{" CrM2 > XPKZ " link gtxtc}    : Same as above but converts to XPKZ format.

               @{" Auto Conv " link gtauto}      : Set this to automatically convert tracks when
                                 : using the INSTALL button.

               @{" Auto Pack " link gtauto}      : Set to pack tracks when being installed.

               @{" Install " link gtinstall}        : Install new tracks.

               @{" View " link gtview}           : View info selected by using the cycle
                                 : gadget below :-
                                 :
                                 : Lap Times
                                 : Storage
                                 : Tracks
                                 : Objects
                                 : Tiles
                                 : Layouts
                                 : Worlds
                                 : Backgrounds
                                 : Sounds
                                 : Missing

               @{" Set Laps " link gtsetlap}       : As you no XTR will only let you play a max
                                 : of 9 laps, but now you can play any amount.

               @{" Start XTR " link gtxtr}           : Start XTR game

               @{" Add EXTN " link gtextn}            : Add XTRU Extension

               @{" Edit Times " link gtedit}     : Allows you to merge and edit some aspects
