@node gtxtc "XTRU - XPKZ->CrM2 and back"
XTRU - XPKZ >< CrM2 conversion
==============================

When you install a new track(s) try and play on them, if XTR complains then
load up XTRU, Then:

 A) Check to make sure you have all objects,tiles...etc
 B) If its `Pack Type' is CrM2 convert it to XPKZ and try again.

When you do convert the track it is changed and all the other files are
tested to see if they are packed then converted. When we get a new track we
always convert it even if the track shows XPKZ because sometimes you will
get an odd Object or Tile that is packed with CrM2. It only takes one and
XTR will not let you play on this track.
@endnode

@node gtauto "XTRU - Auto Conv & Auto Pack"
XTRU - Auto Conv & Auto Pack
============================

The `Auto Conv' gadget is used to set what conversion is to be used on
tracks being install. `AUTO PACK' will pack any files that are not packed
to the same format that `AUTO CONVERT' is set to(This can be slow).

   Please see the @{"Tool Types" link tools} information.
@endnode

@node tools "XTRU - Tool Types"
XTRU - Tool Types
=================

There are three tool types that can be set for XTRU,

   AUTOPACK=ON|OFF
   AUTOCONV=NONE|XPKZ|CrM2
   BUFFER=`SIZE'

As default BUFFER=400. This should not be changed unless XTRU informs you
that `Internal buffer exceeded' in a requester. This buffer is used for
the listview infomation and some of the `Edit Times' functions.

If you are unsure please contact us about this.

@endnode

@node gtinstall "XTRU - Install Gadget"
XTRU - Install Gadget
=====================

Installation is very easy just click on the `Install' gadget, select the full
path where you find the directories for the new tracks,

    Track/
    Objects/
    Tiles/
    etc..

XTRU will install all tracks,objects and tiles etc. It will also convert
them to whatever the `Auto Conv' gadget is set to (None,XPKZ,CrM2).Any
tracks that a unplayable will moved into the `Storage' draw. Also when new
tracks are installed all tracks in `Storage' draw are rechecked to see if
they can be made available for playing, if so they are installed ready for
playing.
@endnode

