@node gtextn "XTRU - Add XTRU Extension"
XTRU - Add XTRU Extension
=========================

This gadget alows you to add a special extension to any tracks that you have
designed. It alows you to store:
                                `Track Name'
                                `Track Version'
                                `Release Date'
                                `Author'
                                `Contact'

So if i made a track called `mega_speed_1.trk' , I could add an extension
like this:
          `Mega Speed #1 (MY FIRST TRACK!)'
          `1.0'
          `21-03-1999'
          `Iain Hammond'
          `e-mail: iain@hashpipe.freeserve.co.uk'

Then everyone will always no whos track it is!

To add an extension just click on the `Add EXTN' gadget and you will be
asked to select a track, It does not matter if is packed or not.

Next you will be asked for all of the above info, Any fields left empty will
have `N/A' inserted. Each field has a maxuimum of 36 chars.

Then XTRU will add the extension, Please note that if the track is packed
it will take a little time because it will need to be unpacked first, Then
it will have the extension added on then repacked.

If a track has an extension already and you want to change it, Just add one
like normal, XTRU will strip off the old one first.

The only way you or any one else can see the extension is to click on XTRU's
`LOAD' gadget and the extension infomation will be displayed along with all
the normal info.
@endnode

@node gtedit "XTRU - Edit Laptimes"
XTRU - Edit Laptimes
====================

   When you press on this gadget another window is opened, the final layout
   of this window is undecided at this time but these gadgets are available.

   @{b}"LOAD"@{ub}
         This lets you load and view any laptime file.

   @{b}"MERGE"@{ub}
