@node remote "XTRU - Remote Install"
XTRU - Remote Install
=====================

XTRU can be started as a `Default Tool' from a Project Icon. So people who
make their own tracks can use XTRU as an installer for there tracks. When
XTRU is started in remote mode the only gadgets available are, AUTO CONV,
AUTO PACK, INSTALL, ABOUT & QUIT. See the Install section about these
gadgets. This type of install is the same as the normal install except XTRU
will no where to find the track files.

Once installed press QUIT and you will be given a choice to either exit or
enter XTRU. An icon is supplied for inclusion with third party track
archives, this can be found in the ICONS draw.

How to include it in your archive.
==================================
To use just copy the icon into your directory that contains the tracks,
,objects etc. draws. There is a supplied icon in the icons draw with the
XTRU archive.
@endnode

@node alone "XTRU - Stand Alone Installer"
XTRU - Stand Alone Installer
============================

This is a completely separate program to the main XTRU program, and it does
not need the main XTRU program to run. All this does is install your tracks
automatically for other people straight into there XTR directory, it also
converts them into the `XPKZ' format to guarantee that they will work with
all versions of XTR. There are no options to convert to `CrM2' or to pack
the tracks it just installs them.

To include this with your track archives you must copy these files from the
draw `Stand_Alone_Installer" in the main XTRU draw.

The files are:-
               1) XTRU_TRACK_INSTALLER
               2) XTRU_TRACK_INSTALLER.info
               3) XTRU_Order.ReadMe
               4) XTRU_Order.ReadMe.info

These files need to be placed in your archive draw that contains the track,
object etc. draws.

Its as simple as that!
@endnode

